node.text: At midnight European time, you can listen to La Comitiva’s version of For The Time Being. The original was made together with @phonique in 2004. Our acoustic version reveals also its initial inspiration, “quetzal” by Los Hermanos. A techno-track that also inspired Island by The Whitest Boy Alive. My tinnitus problems has for many years cut me out from the electronic music scene. But with La Comitiva the (invisible) beat goes on... Cover-artwork by the amazing @clara.cebrian @bubbles_records @lacomitiva.band @antonio.pulli #saaldrei #funkhaus #nilsfrahm

If you have attended a show of Kings of Convenience or La Comitiva recently, you must have noticed Andrea Moschella @say_yes.eu that travels with us and sells merchandise at our shows. He produces t-shirts, posters and tote bags in Siracusa in cooperation with designers around the world. Now he has created the online store https://say-yes.eu/ where you can find items not only from us but also from Kakkmaddafakka, Kommode, Dena and The Whitest Boy Alive.

L’estate è finita, domani te ne vai, verso il nord-Italia. Dove si può trovare: un posto di lavoro e l’università, concerti importanti, ragazze interessanti. “Paradiso” is finally out and can be listened to Spotify and other places. Check the link in bio. From yesterdays show at anfiteatro del Venda. We had so much fun when the public got close to the stage. @luciamoschella did her dance from the La Prima Estate video. Members of @we_are_stargaze joined us adding oboe, flute and trombone. @lacomitiva.band finally back in it’s homeland. Now we are on our way to Cesenatico( Friday) then to Firenze ( Saturday) and finally Milano Castello Sforzesco ( Monday). Great pictures by @michelepiazza

We have been working for weeks now preparing for this show. La Comitiva will join forces with Stargaze presenting most of the songs that will end up on my/our upcoming record. Ukulele, cavaquinho, classical guitar, steel string guitar, flute, oboe, trumpet, trombone, cello, viola and violin. Since there are so many new songs, it will be hard to follow even for the most musical persons. So it will be allowed to record the show with your phone or a small recording device( as long as you don’t bother the person on your neighbouring seat) so you can take it home with you and digest it there. Another special thing, that I learned when I played the Elbphilharmonie with Kings of Convenience, is that we will perform standing in a circle. This because the audience is seated all around the stage. Amazing poster again by @garami82 ...bis Montag!
